Woodstock resident Genevieve Bootcov took the decision two years ago, just as Covid-19 hit, to open up the doors to her home to help vulnerable children, specifically abandoned newborn babies. eNCA's Tanya Nefdt reports. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - At the start of the pandemic, when most people were worried about how they were going to hold onto their jobs,
a Cape Town woman resigned as a night nurse to open a safe home for children in need. Statistics show that the number of abandoned children has increased significantly during the pandemic. Around 300 children are abandoned every month in South Africa. Woodstock resident Genevieve Bootcov labour of love has now grown into a NPO called Little Hands Baby Home. * eNCA's Tanya Nefdt reports.